HEADWORD: Underbid
<hw>Un`der*bid"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To bid less
than, as when a contract or service is offered to the lowest bidder; to
offer to contract, sell, or do for a lower price than.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underbind</ent>⟦br⟧
